description:
A Titan Rides the Train!

The Leader tells his origin and wants to conquer the south-western missile base. Doctor Banner is put under the surveillance of Major Glenn Talbot by General Ross, when he has to supervise the transport of a great nuclear devise. The leader sends his invincible Humanoid to steal the device from the train it is on. The stress of being attacked by a robot makes Banner turn into the Hulk and the Hulk then attacks the Leader's Humanoid. When their fight loosens the screws on the nuclear devise, the part of Hulk's mind, which is still Bruce Banner, makes him realize what is about to happen to the devise and the Hulk jumps back onto the train, to bring it to safety. Exhausted the Hulk transforms back into Bruce Banner, just before the army arrives. Major Takbot misunderstands the situation and puts Doctor Banner into prison. Meanwhile the Leader wants to learn more about the green monster.

The Horde of Humanoids!

General Ross and Major Talbot visit Bruce Banner in his cell to tell him, that he is accused for treason and will have to stand in court. In that moment a letter arrives for the General, which says that the trial is postponed, so Doctor Banner can supervise the test on the nuclear absorbitor he invented. Meanwhile the Leader gets contacted by the Chameleon about Banner visiting Astra Island and sends a horde of Humanoids to again try to steal Banner's device. On the island is Doctor Banner starting the test, when Major Talbot accuses him of working with the Hulk, which stresses Banner so much, that he turns into the Hulk, but not until he could hide from the Major's eyes. The Leader's Humanoids arrive at the island and get the order to seize the Hulk and bring him to the Leader.

On the Rampage!

The Hulk fights against the Humanoids, when the army arrives at the scene to capture the Hulk, the fighting parties fall into the sea and the Hulk swims away, feeling that he will soon change back into the puny Doctor Banner. Changing back from the Hulk, Bruce Banner swims to the surface, where an enemy ship fishes him out of the water. The Leader contacts Banner's captors and warns them, that they will regret it. Banner's captors try to threaten him with getting no food, but he doesn't give in, so they put him into a tiny cell. In the cell changes Banner into the Hulk and the green goliath breaks through the walls. The antagonistic army tries to kill the Hulk with a vaporizing cannon, but he uses a thunderclap to destroy the whole enemy base.
name: A Titan Rides the Train!; The Horde of Humanoids!; On the Rampage!

description:
The Power of Doctor Banner!

The army discusses the further procedure regarding Bruce Banner, who is still behind enemy lines. Meanwhile, he Hulk is still smashing through the enemies base. As Hulk finds the head of the base behind some debris, he starts transforming back into Bruce Banner, who can't stop the heavy concrete wall from squashing the soldier. Banner sits in the ruins of the base, as enemy bomber start shooting and kill innocent civilians, enraged about what he sees Banner changes back into Hulk and attacks them. In the meantime General Ross and Major Talbot inform Betty Ross, that Banner is a traitor and has to be dealt with.

Where Strides the Behemoth

Hitting airplanes in midair and smashing tanks on the ground, Hulk fight against the enemy without mercy. With a thunderclap he destroys the remaining tanks and sends the soldiers fleeing. Feeling the need to go home, Hulk starts jumping from country to country, until he ends up in the Himalayas. Turning back into Bruce Banner, some Asians appear and forcefully escort him to the next american embassy, where they demand a ransom from the american army. Major Talbot come to take Banner back to the USA as some Arabians appear and demand the ransom from the Asians. Talbot and Banner use this to flee, but the rock below them crumbles. Talbot manages to get a grip on a rock, but Banner falls down into an abyss.

Back from the Dead!

Still falling to his sure death, Bruce Banner changes once again into the incredible Hulk. The Hulk manages to get a grip at a rock wall, simultaneous the rock below Major Talbot starts tu crumble and now he falls down and faints. Hulk sees the falling Major and catches him in midair. Not understanding why the man he just saved doesn't answer, Hulk lies him on the ground and then heads for home, jumping from island to island. Rescued by the US Airforce, Major Talbot is brought home and speaks to the press about Banner's seemingly betrayal. Meanwhile the Hulk found his way back to Banner's house. Lying down onto the couch and changes back into Bruce Banner, as soon as he's asleep. The scientist doesn't get a moment to rest, when the army enters his home and takes him into custody. In his cell Doctor Banner reads the interview, which Major Talbot gave the newspaper and the anger over those false words, makes him turn into the Hulk. When Talbot enters the prison he gets kidnapped by Hulk. General Ross then shoots a sonic beam at the mountains where Hulk is hiding. Caught in the blast, the Hulk blacks out and when General Ross and his daughter arrive, he is Bruce Banner once again. They tell him that he's free of all charges and Talbot thanks him, for saving his life. All hope that Hulk is buried below the debris and never comes back.
name: The Power of Doctor Banner!; Where Strides the Behemoth; Back from the Dead!

description:
Micro-Monsters

While Doctor Bruce Banner prepares himself for the test of his Absorbatron, the green-tinted Leader makes his own preparations to steal Banner's device. He shrinks his Humanoids, loads them into his plane and scatters them onto the testing ground. After Banner and Talbot entered the room below the testing ground, the Humanoids start to grow and attack Talbot and Banner. The Leader orders that they either capture Doctor Banner or destroy him. In that moment the frail scientist changes once again into the incredible Hulk, only to be brought down by sleeping gas, released by the Leader's Humanoids. The Leader then transports Bannerâ€™s Absorbatron and the Hulk, with a magnetic beam into his lair.

The Lair of the Leader

A strike force enters the testing ground on the search for Doctor Banner and Major Talbot. The Major still believes that Banner is a traitor and works with the Hulk. Meanwhile in Banner's hidden cave, Rick Jones still waits for a radio signal from Bruce Banner, not noticing, that the Leader lands in his own hidden Lair, not far away. In his lab the he starts examining the Hulk and wants to either recreate him or control him. The sleeping gas slows Hulk's heartbeat down and he transforms back into Banner, who uses his chance to send a Morse code message to the army. Rick Jones also hears his message and goes to a vantage point, only to see, that the whole missile command is on the search for Banner. As the Leader notices that the Hulk isn't on the examining table anymore, he fulls the room with a double dose of sleeping gas, but unlike before the gas doesn't make Banner sleepy, but makes him change into the Hulk again. In the fight, which then starts between the two green skinned men, destroys Hulk the Absorbatron, so that the Leader never can get a hand on it.

To Live Again

The army, foremost Major Talbot, still believes that Banner is a traitor and that he and the Hulk work together. Meanwhile searches the Hulk for the Leader to destroy him. The green tinted madman with the big head however, sends an enlarged Humanoid to destroy the missile base and Hulk. The army shoots a missile at the large Humanoid and Hulk, who just saved Rick. The missile explodes and sends Hulk and Rick Jones into the sky. When they crash onto the ground, Jones gets hurt and is near dead. The Hulk, scared for his friends life, changes back into Bruce Banner and the released radiation from his transformation saves the teenagers life.
name: Micro-Monsters; The Lair of the Leader; To Live Again

description:
Brawn Against Brain

Hidden in a cave in the desert, changes the Hulk back into Bruce Banner. At the military base, speaks General Ross bad about Dr. Banner and wants to test the Doctors robot without him, in that moment arrives the scientist at the base. In the Lab works Bruce Banner on the last few adjustments and broods over being the Hulk, as the General enters his lab and tells Bruce the new robot test date. Working until night on the robot, Dr. Banner hears something. Suspecting a spy he chases after the figure. Getting tense by chasing the spy, Bruce Banner turns again into the Hulk, who then wants to get out as fast as possible, to flex his muscles. In the mean time the unknown person overpowers an unsuspcting watchman and climbs into the robot. At the next day on the robot test, the man in the robot armor walks away with it, General Ross immediately suspects Banner to be the thief and traitor. Wanting to stop the robot, Ross sends remote controlled tanks after it, but the robot destroys them without trouble. Close by notices the Hulk the robot, somehow remembering, that the robot is Banner's work, he assumes, the scientist build it, to the defeat the Hulk, not knowing that he himself is Brue Banner. The Hulk fights against the robot, but with no success. The stress, being too much for him, changes him back into Bruce Banner, who is then found by the army, General Ross accusing him instantly to be a traitor.

Captured At Last!

The man in the robot walks through the desert and stumbles over one of Doctor Banner's hidden labs and decides to use the devices in there to build something to destroy the nearby army base. Meanwhile, Bruce Banner works feverishly in the military base lab on adevice to take down the robot. In his office talk General Ross and Major Talbot about Bruce Banner being a spy, when Betty Ross enters the room, Talbot asks her to show him the base, which her father agrees on for her. In the desert searches Bruce Banner for his missing robot with his detector, as an army helicoper, with Major Talbot and Ms. Ross inside, spots him and decides to land nearby. The man in the robot also notices the helicoper and assumes that they're after him, so he lifts a rock, to smash the helicopter. This is seen by Bruce Banner, who turns into the Hulk. The green goliath then jumps through the rock, stopping it's fall and savong Ms. Ross. When debris falls down on them, Major Talbot protecs Betty Ross with his body, hurting his shoulder in doing so. Hulk and the robot end up in a cave, the Hulk pounding on the robots armor, not able to hurt the man inside. With a shoulder bump, the robot shoves the Hulk over the edge of a bottomless pit. The Hulk is barely able to hold himself on the edge, when the man approaches him, bit a giant rock in the robots hands. When missiles, which the man in the robot had set off ontop of the cave, ignite, the Hulk has to think fast to stop the missiles. He jumps over to the other side of the pit, to bounce back to the robot and shove him into the pit. The hulk jumps into the fired missile to stop it. Unconscious from the blow, the Hulk plummets to earth. Major Talbot finds the unconscious Hulk laying on the ground. Soldiers tie up the Hulk with special chains made by Bruce Banner.

Enter the Chameleon!

Regaining his consciousness, the Hulk finds himself in chains. Struggling with freeing himself from the chains, the Hulk feels how he changes back into Bruce Banner. Meanwhile thousands of miles away from the missile base, a mysterious figure barks orders into a powerful transmitter. It is the Leader contacting the Chameleon, to figure out what happened to the man who was supposed to steal the robot. The Chameleon flies to the United States and the army base where they brought the captured Hulk. Disguising himself as General Ross, the Chameleon wants to make the Hulk his ally, but before he reaches the green goliath, the Hulk transforms back into Bruce Banner. The lean scientist slips out of the chains and goes to hide himself in his room, so the General doesn't find out who the Hulk really is. In his office, the real Thunderbolt Ross boils with rage, because the Hulk has escaped. When doctor Banner enters the office, he's met with false accusations by Major Talbot, which make the doctor to leave the room. As soon as the good doctor wants to enter his own room, he gets attacked by the Chameleon, who disguises himself as Bruce Banner, after he owerpowered and bound the helpless scientist. Betty Ross enters Banner's lab, to the search for him, meeting the disguised Chameleon, but immideatly looks through his act and the Chameleon grabs her. Bruce Banner, still bound in a room next to his lab, fears for Betty's safety and transforms once again into the incredible Hulk. The green goliath tears the rope apart and breaks through the wall, between the room and the lab. The Hulk is just about to attack the Chameleon, when he sees an army jeep and flees the scenes, not wanting to be captured again. The Chameleon thinks he has driven off the Hulk by himself. He steals a Gamma-Grenade to the Leader and but the abducted Betty Ross into arocket car, to get rid of her. In that moment jumps the Hulk onto the rocket car tracks and stops the fast vehicle. The Chameleon threats the Hulk with the Gamma-Grenade. In fear for his life, the villain throws the bomb and flees. The Hulk remembers what Banner said about the bomb and jumps on it to contain the explosion. The released gamma rays change once more the incredible Hulk back to the frail Doctor Bruce Banner, who then flees the scene. Unseen and unrewarded for his heroic deed.

description: Meridiana is beset by swarms of hostile birds that attack anyone who steps outside. Eventually after a visit from Cybersix, Lucas deduces the birds are being controlled by JosÃ©, who's control is paused only whenever new broadcasts are transmitted. Lucas creates diversions to allow Cybersix to get to the TV tower and electrical broadcaster to deactivate the control signal, but Cybersix and Data-7 are forced to battle JosÃ©'s giant bird abomination.
name: Blue Birds of Horror

description: Meridiana's top six detectives, including Julian's friend Henrique, are brainwashed by JosÃ©'s new mind-control device to seek out Cybersix. Julian catches wind of this but is captured by JosÃ© and becomes bait to lure Cybersix into a trap.
name: Brainwashed

description: A horde of winged goblins attack Cybersix but they retreat at dawn. Julian finds the goblins' lair and is trapped by them, but Data-7 rescues him. After a second encounter with the goblins, Cybersix realizes their weakness to sunlight. Cybersix brings a train to the goblin lair and as she keeps the goblins at bay, Data-7 and Julian load the eggs on the train. Cybersix traps the goblins on the train and destroys them and their eggs in the sunlight.
name: Gone with the Wings

description: JosÃ© receives from his father an eyeball creature capable of draining its victims' consciousness and growing in the process. During a fight with it, Cybersix reflects the eye's gaze back at it with mirrored glass, causing the eye to go haywire. The eye then intensifies its power at a stadium. As JosÃ© struggles to capture the now out of control eye, Cybersix seeks to destroy it before it feeds on the rest of the city's remaining population.
name: The Eye

description: A werewolf monster stalks the streets at night and turns other people into werewolves. Meanwhile, a new teacher named Elaine signs on to work at the high school and begins dating Lucas, making Adrian envious. Lucas winds up turning into a werewolf and Cybersix realizes Elaine is the werewolf monster. Cybersix is now forced to battle both Elaine and Lucas in their werewolf states.
name: Full Moon Fascination

description: JosÃ© captures Data-7 and stages a robotic circus show in Meridiana. Cybersix comes to the rescue, but is overwhelmed by robotic animals and winds up being used in the attraction. Lucas is taken backstage when he attempts to intervene, but manages to free Data-7. Lucas then disables the robots' programming, while Data-7 rescues Cybersix. The three of them now however have to deal with a circus full of out of control robots.
name: The Greatest Show in Meridiana

So even if Cybersix manages to save Meridiana, she may not be able to save herself.
